<item>
            <title>[SPR-13670] @ContextConfiguration defined on a base class and a composed annotation do not merge</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-13670</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When a test has multiple @ContextConfiguration annotations defined on a base class and a composed annotation then the one defined on the composed annotation is ignored.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I created a small example that illustrates the issue (see reference URL). In this case the &lt;a href=&quot;https://gist.github.com/alainsahli/a3d8fd26adc527aa422c#file-testappcontext-java&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;TestAppContext&lt;/a&gt; defined on the &lt;a href=&quot;https://gist.github.com/alainsahli/a3d8fd26adc527aa422c#file-composedannotation-java&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;ComposedAnnotation&lt;/a&gt; is ignored and therefore the &lt;a href=&quot;https://gist.github.com/alainsahli/a3d8fd26adc527aa422c#file-composedannotationtest-java&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;ComposedAnnotationTest&lt;/a&gt; fails because the needed bean does not exist.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If the test class is directly annotated with @ContextConfiguration instead of using the &lt;a href=&quot;https://gist.github.com/alainsahli/a3d8fd26adc527aa422c#file-composedannotation-java&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;ComposedAnnotation&lt;/a&gt; it works (see &lt;a href=&quot;https://gist.github.com/alainsahli/a3d8fd26adc527aa422c#file-workingtest-java&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;WorkingTest&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
